78
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:16,200
Do you always listen
to other's conversations?

79
00:09:17,129 --> 00:09:20,246
Do you want to go
to the end of the line?

80
00:09:21,049 --> 00:09:24,758
-Why do you want to know?
-It sounded a little deep for--

81
00:09:27,649 --> 00:09:31,085
It just sounded a little deep
for a Friday night.

82
00:09:31,929 --> 00:09:36,286
Religion is important in our culture,
at least in my family.

83
00:09:36,529 --> 00:09:39,441
Your destiny
has already been decided.

84
00:09:39,689 --> 00:09:42,157
You just have to read the signs.

85
00:09:44,649 --> 00:09:46,526
You don't believe that?

86
00:09:47,649 --> 00:09:51,403
If a bus hits a guy,
it's because he wasn't looking.

87
00:09:51,649 --> 00:09:53,765
Not because of a master plan.

88
00:09:54,009 --> 00:09:58,605
It wasn't fate that you were in
this line when I got off the phone?

89
00:10:00,169 --> 00:10:04,242
No, I think it was more
of a bladder thing.

90
00:10:05,369 --> 00:10:09,078
That's too bad.
Because, you see...

91
00:10:09,769 --> 00:10:15,719
...l think there's an explanation
beyond reason, beyond all logic...

92
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:19,964
...that brought you
to this very spot...

93
00:10:20,329 --> 00:10:25,449
...at the exact same time
I showed up at this very spot.

94
00:10:26,449 --> 00:10:30,044
-You do?
-Absolutely.

95
00:10:31,049 --> 00:10:33,882
And why would fate go
to all that trouble?

96
00:10:35,849 --> 00:10:39,319
So I wouldn't have
to wait in line.

97
00:10:42,649 --> 00:10:43,638
Thanks.

